      "number": "7",
      "text": "7 (1) An inspector must be provided with a certificate, in the prescribed form, of the inspector's designation showing the purposes, classes of dangerous goods, road vehicles or rail vehicles and the buildings or places for which the inspector has been designated.\n(2) On entering or inspecting any building, place, container, packaging, road vehicle or rail vehicle an inspector must, if so required, produce the certificate to the person in charge of the thing or material being entered or inspected.",
      "part": "Part 3 — Inspection, Detention and Removal",
